证据片段: The alloy Excel (Zr3.5Sn-0.8Mo-0.8Nb) is stronger and more creep resistant than Zr-2.5Nb

证据片段: The tensile strength of the annealed tubes met the CANDU-PHW minimum specifications but was a little lower than the average cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb pressure tube.

文献ID: STP754-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_5th Volume_017_chunk4
证据片段: Results from other Excel tubes installed in NRU and WR-1 and the results from small stress relaxation and growth specimens show that the dimensional stability of these tubes during service in a reactor should be much better than that of cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb.

文献ID: STP754-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_5th Volume_017_chunk4
证据片段: The dimensional changes of the Excel tubes after 20 years' service in a 600-MWe CANDU-PHW reactor are predicted to be considerably less than those for cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb pressure tubes, Table 9, particularly the annealed tubes.

证据片段: Although the corrosion rate of the Excel tubes in CANDU-PHW reactor coolant is about twice that of cold-worked $\mathbf { Z } \mathbf { r } { - } 2 . 5 \mathbf { N } \mathbf { b }$ tubes, the hydrogen pickup rates are similar.

文献ID: STP754-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_5th Volume_017_chunk4
证据片段: Therefore the 30-year corrosion allowance for the inside of Excel pressure tubes would have to be about $0 . 2 \mathsf { m m }$ compared with $0 . 1 \mathrm { \ m m }$ for cold-worked Zr-2.5Nb pressure tubes.
